Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED: 1 . A tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium storing instructions that, when executed by one or more processors, cause the one or more processors to: receive indications of positions, in a first coordinate system, of a first sensor and a second sensor disposed at a flexible elongate device; determine, based on intra-operative imaging data, an indication of a position, in a second coordinate system, of a fiducial of the flexible elongate device, wherein the fiducial is disposed at a separation distance, along the flexible elongate device, from the first sensor; and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the indications of the positions of the first sensor and the second sensor in the first coordinate system, the indication of the position of the fiducial in the second coordinate system, and the separation distance. 2. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of claim 1 , wherein the fiducial comprises a distributed fiducial configured to be indicative of at least two positions along the flexible elongate device, and wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to: determine, based on the intra-operative imaging data, indications of the at least two positions of the distributed fiducial, and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indications of the at least two positions of the distributed fiducial. 3. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of claim 2, wherein the fiducial is configured to be indicative of at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device, and wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to: determine, based on the intra-operative imaging data, indications of the at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device, and 

 register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indications of the at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device. 4. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of any one of claims 1 - 3, wherein the fiducial is configured to be indicative of orientation, and wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to: determine, based on the intra-operative imaging data, an indication of orientation of the fiducial, and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indication of orientation of the fiducial. 5. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of claim 4 wherein the fiducial is configured to have a rotationally asymmetrical shape around an axis of the flexible elongate device, and determining the indication of orientation of the fiducial is based at least in part on the rotationally asymmetrical shape. 6. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of any one of claims 1 - 5, wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to generate, based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, an alert indicative of one or more of a position or an orientation of at least a portion of the flexible elongate device. 7. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of any one of claims 1 - 6, wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to: compute a metric indicative of uncertainty in registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system; compare the computed metric to a threshold; and 

 generate, based at least in part on comparing the computed metric to the threshold, an alert indicative of the computed metric exceeding the threshold. 8. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of any one of claims 1 - 7, wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to generate, on a display unit and based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, a graphical user interface displaying at least a portion of the flexible elongate device including positions of the first sensor, the second sensor and the fiducial in a joint coordinate system. 9. A medical device comprising: a flexible elongate body having an axis; a position sensor disposed at the flexible elongate body of the medical device, the position sensor configured to generate an indication of position in a first coordinate system; and a fiducial disposed at the flexible elongate body of the medical device and having a rotationally asymmetrical shape with respect to the axis of the flexible elongate body of the medical device. 10. The medical device of claim 9, wherein the fiducial includes a ring element rotationally symmetrical with the axis of the flexible elongate body of the medical device and a rotationally asymmetrical element with respect to the axis of the flexible elongate body of the medical device. 11 . The medical device of claim 10, wherein the rotationally asymmetrical element comprises one or more of a dot or a line. 12. The medical device of claim 10 or 11 , wherein the rotationally asymmetrical element is physically detached from the ring element. 13. The medical device of any one of claims 9-12, wherein the fiducial includes an open ring in a plane substantially perpendicular to the axis of the flexible elongate body of the medical device. 14. The medical device of any one of claims 9-13, wherein the fiducial includes a metallic element. 15. The medical device of any one of claims 9-14, wherein at least a portion of the fiducial is disposed at a sleeve removably attached to the flexible elongate body of the medical device. 16. The medical device of any one of claims 9-15, wherein at least a portion of the fiducial is disposed at a stylet removably insertable through the flexible elongate body of the medical device. 17. The medical device of any one of claims 9-16, wherein the fiducial includes at least two elements disposed at the flexible elongate body of the medical device, and wherein the position sensor is disposed at the flexible elongate body of the medical device between two of the at least two elements of the fiducial. 18. A method comprising: receiving, by one or more processors, indications of positions, in a first coordinate system, of a first sensor and a second sensor disposed at a flexible elongate device; determining, based on intra-operative imaging data and by the one or more processors, an indication of position, in a second coordinate system, of a fiducial of the flexible elongate device, wherein the fiducial is disposed at the flexible elongate device at a separation distance from the first sensor; and registering, by the one or more processors, the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the indications of positions of the first sensor and 

the second sensor in the first coordinate system, the indication of position of the fiducial in the second coordinate system, and the separation distance. 19. The method of claim 18, wherein the fiducial comprises a distributed fiducial configured to be indicative of at least two positions along the flexible elongate device, the method further comprising: determining, based on the intra-operative imaging data, indications of the at least two positions of the distributed fiducial, and registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indications of the at least two positions of the distributed fiducial. 20. The method of claim 19, wherein the fiducial is configured to be indicative of at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device, the method further comprising: determining, based on the intra-operative imaging data, indications of the at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device, and registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indications of the at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device. 21 . The method of any one of claims 18-20, wherein the fiducial is configured to be indicative of orientation, the method further comprising: determining, based on the intra-operative imaging data, an indication of orientation of the fiducial, and registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indication of orientation of the fiducial. 22. The method of claim 21 wherein the fiducial is configured to have a rotationally asymmetrical shape around an axis of the flexible elongate device, and determining the indication of orientation of the fiducial is based at least in part on the rotationally asymmetrical shape. 23. The method of any one of claims 18-22, wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to generate, based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, an alert indicative of one or more of a position or an orientation of at least a portion of the flexible elongate device. 24. The method of any one of claims 18-23, further comprising: computing a metric indicative of uncertainty in registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system; comparing the computed metric to a threshold; and generating, based at least in part on comparing the computed metric to the threshold, an alert indicative of the computed metric exceeding the threshold. 25. The method of claim 18, further comprising: generating, based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, on a display unit and by the one or more processors, a graphical user interface displaying at least a portion of the flexible elongate device including positions of the first sensor, the second sensor and the fiducial in a joint coordinate system. 26. A medical system, comprising: a flexible elongate device; a first sensor and a second sensor disposed at the flexible elongate device; a fiducial disposed at the flexible elongate device at a separation distance from the first sensor; and one or more processors configured to: receive indications of positions, in a first coordinate system, of the first sensor and the second sensor; 

 determine, based on intra-operative imaging data, a position of the fiducial in a second coordinate system; and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based on the received indications of positions of the first sensor and the second sensor in the first coordinate system, the determined position of the fiducial in the second coordinate system, and the separation distance. 27. The medical system of claim 26, wherein the fiducial comprises a distributed fiducial configured to be indicative of at least two positions along the flexible elongate device, and wherein the one or more processors are configured to: determine, based on the intra-operative imaging data, indications of the at least two positions of the distributed fiducial, and register, based at least in part on the determined indications of the at least two positions of the distributed fiducial, the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system. 28. The medical system of claim 27, wherein the fiducial is configured to be indicative of at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device, and wherein the one or more processors are configured to: determine, based on the intra-operative imaging data, indications of the at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device, and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indications of the at least two distinct distances along the flexible elongate device. 29. The medical system of any one of claims 26-28, wherein the fiducial is configured to be indicative of orientation, and wherein the one or more processors are configured to: determine, based on the intra-operative imaging data, an indication of orientation of the fiducial, and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the determined indication of orientation of the fiducial. 30. The medical system of claim 29 wherein the fiducial is configured to have a rotationally asymmetrical shape around an axis of the flexible elongate device, and determining the indication of orientation of the fiducial is based at least in part on the rotationally asymmetrical shape. 31 . The medical system of any one of claims 26-30, wherein the one or more processors are configured to generate, based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, an alert indicative of one or more of a position or an orientation of at least a portion of the flexible elongate device. 32. The medical system of any one of claims 26-31 , wherein the one or more processors are configured to: compute a metric indicative of uncertainty in registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system; compare the computed metric to a threshold; and generate, based at least in part on comparing the computed metric to the threshold, an alert indicative of the computed metric exceeding the threshold. 33. The medical system of any one of claims 26-32, wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to generate, on a display unit and based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, a graphical user interface displaying at least a portion of the flexible elongate device including positions of the first sensor, the second sensor and the fiducial in a joint coordinate system. 34. A tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium storing instructions that, when executed by one or more processors, cause the one or more processors to: receive an indication of a position, in a first coordinate system, of a position sensor disposed at a flexible elongate body of a medical device; 

 determine, based on intra-operative imaging data, an indication of a position, in a second coordinate system, of a fiducial disposed at the flexible elongate body and having a rotationally asymmetrical shape with respect to an axis of the flexible elongate body; and register the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the indication of the position of the position sensor and the indication of the position of the fiducial in the second coordinate system. 35. The tangible, non-transitory, computer readable medium of claim 34, wherein the instructions, when executed by the one or more processors, further cause the one or more processors to generate, on a display unit and based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, a graphical user interface displaying at least a portion of the flexible elongate device including positions of the sensor and the fiducial in a joint coordinate system. 36. A method comprising: receiving, by one or more processors, an indication of a position, in a first coordinate system, of a position sensor disposed at a flexible elongate body of a medical device; determining, based on intra-operative imaging data and by the one or more processors, an indication of a position, in a second coordinate system, of a fiducial disposed at the flexible elongate body and having a rotationally asymmetrical shape with respect to an axis of the flexible elongate body; and registering, by the one or more processors, the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system based at least in part on the indication of the position of the position sensor and the indication of the position of the fiducial in the second coordinate system. 37. The method of claim 36, further comprising: generating, on a display unit and based at least in part on registering the first coordinate system to the second coordinate system, a graphical user interface displaying at least a portion of the flexible elongate device including positions of the sensor and the fiducial in a joint coordinate system.
